# Manual directory

`Manual/` is the user manual for this project, structured like the [eBookED](https://github.com/JohnDovey/eBookED) app's own manual (`eBookEd/manual/` in that repo): `frontmatter/` (title page, copyright, TOC, introduction), `chapters/` (numbered `NNN-Title.ebhtml`), `backmatter/` (about, appendices), `images/`, `output/` (exported builds).

**`.ebhtml` is a plain HTML fragment, NOT Markdown.** Numbered chapter files have a small `---`-delimited header followed by raw HTML body:

```
---
title: Getting Started
subtitle:
numberMode: Auto
numberOverride:
---
<h1 id="getting-started">Getting Started</h1>
<p>Body content as plain HTML...</p>
```

Front matter and back matter pages are just a bare HTML fragment with no header.

This manual is ideally authored and exported using the eBookED app itself (open `Manual/` as a project via File → New/Open Project), not hand-edited.

**Build outputs are committed, not gitignored.** `Manual/output/` holds the exported `.epub`, `.pdf`, and `.docx` — these are generated by the user and belong in the repo, bundled with releases. This is the opposite of eBookED's own repo (which gitignores its `manual/output/`) — do not apply that gitignore rule here.

Add or update the relevant numbered chapter whenever a user-facing feature is added or changed, and keep `output/` current when new builds are generated.
